					<description><![CDATA[<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/knapp-sawmill-moved-to-glen-haven/">c. 1896</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-0"><div class="row col-no-gutter no-top-padding no-bottom-padding no-h-padding full-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 no-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light shift_y_neg_half"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column alpha-anim animate_when_almost_visible" ><h4><strong><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62d3df9341435">Knapp Sawmill Moved To Glen Haven</div></strong></h4>
<div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbafef995f0">The Knapps moved their sawmill from Idlewild to present day Glen Haven.</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div>

<script id="script-row-unique-0" data-row="script-row-unique-0" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-0"));</script></div></div></div>




<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-1"><div class="row col-no-gutter no-top-padding no-bottom-padding no-h-padding full-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-1/5 no-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1658132744002 border-color-gyho-color left-t-right animate_when_almost_visible"  style="border-style: solid;margin-right: 10% ;margin-left: 10% ;border-top-width: 4px ;border-right-width: 0px ;border-bottom-width: 0px ;border-left-width: 0px ;padding-top: 10px ;"><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb251e2350">Later in 1896, after two removed, the Knapps brought the saw mill to Glen Haven, and in 1897 made the claims on the land which became the subdivision comprising what is now the Glen Haven Resort</div>
</div><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1658132966338 right-t-left animate_when_almost_visible"  style="margin-right: 10% ;margin-left: 10% ;"><p style="text-align: left;"><em><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb29fe2351">Joseph G. Knapp, The Glen Haven Story, 1967</div></em></p>
</div><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1617356820233 border-color-gyho-color right-t-left animate_when_almost_visible"  style="border-style: solid;margin-right: 10% ;margin-left: 10% ;border-top-width: 0px ;border-right-width: 0px ;border-bottom-width: 1px ;border-left-width: 0px ;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-1" data-row="script-row-unique-1" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-1"));</script></div></div></div>



<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/knapp-sawmill-moved-to-glen-haven/">c. 1896</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>December 27th, 1894</title>
		<link>https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/december-27th-1894-the-knapps-partner-with-rannells-on-the-sawmill/</link>
		
