		<item>
		<title>July 5th, 1894</title>
		<link>https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/july-5th-1894-rannells-toll-road-reaches-idlewild/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathaniel Dauth]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 02 Apr 2021 15:15:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/?post_type=cool_timeline&#038;p=584</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/july-5th-1894-rannells-toll-road-reaches-idlewild/">July 5th, 1894</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-4"><div class="row col-no-gutter no-top-padding no-bottom-padding no-h-padding full-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 no-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light shift_y_neg_half"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column alpha-anim animate_when_almost_visible" ><h4><strong><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62d3df9341435">Rannells Toll Road Reaches Idlewild</div></strong></h4>
<div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbafef995f0">Rannells Toll Road reaches the 7 mile mark which would place it at present day Idlewild.</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div>

<script id="script-row-unique-4" data-row="script-row-unique-4" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-4"));</script></div></div></div>



<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-5"><div class="row no-top-padding no-bottom-padding no-h-padding full-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-6 single-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light animate_when_almost_visible alpha-anim"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode-single-media  text-right"><div class="single-wrapper" style="max-width: 100%;"><div class="tmb tmb-light  tmb-shadowed tmb-shadowed-sm tmb-media-first tmb-media-last tmb-content-overlay tmb-no-bg"><div class="t-inside"><div class="t-entry-visual"><div class="t-entry-visual-tc"><div class="uncode-single-media-wrapper"><img class="wp-image-1861" src="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1894-07-05-Loveland-Reporter-Toll-Road-up-to-Idlewild.jpg" width="272" height="272" alt="" srcset="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1894-07-05-Loveland-Reporter-Toll-Road-up-to-Idlewild.jpg 272w, https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1894-07-05-Loveland-Reporter-Toll-Road-up-to-Idlewild-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1894-07-05-Loveland-Reporter-Toll-Road-up-to-Idlewild-250x250.jpg 250w" sizes="(max-width: 272px) 100vw, 272px" /></div>
					</div>
				</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-6 no-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light animate_when_almost_visible right-t-left"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1658054420531 text-small"  style="margin-bottom: -15px ;"><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb120995f2">The Toll Road</div>
</div><div class="uncode_text_column text-small" ><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb19f995f3">The new road is now passable for about seven miles. A few more shares of stock sold and the work will be rushed through to completion-and the stockholders and the Loveland business men will be great gainers. The prices of toll now in force are (for the roundtrip) single rigs 25c; double rigs, 50c. The best fishing grounds can be found along the road.</div>
</div><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1658054434023 text-small"  style="margin-top: 20px ;"><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb21b995f4">Loveland Reporter - July 5, 1894</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-5" data-row="script-row-unique-5" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-5"));</script></div></div></div>




<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/july-5th-1894-rannells-toll-road-reaches-idlewild/">July 5th, 1894</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>c. 1893</title>
		<link>https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/1893-knapp-sawmill-at-idlewild/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathaniel Dauth]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 02 Apr 2021 15:05:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/?post_type=cool_timeline&#038;p=582</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/1893-knapp-sawmill-at-idlewild/">c. 1893</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-6"><div class="row col-no-gutter no-top-padding no-bottom-padding no-h-padding full-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 no-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light shift_y_neg_half"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column alpha-anim animate_when_almost_visible" ><h4><strong><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62d3df9341435">Knapp Sawmill At Idlewild</div></strong></h4>
<div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbafef995f0">Orren Smith Knapp, Ira Owen Knapp, and a party of men setup a sawmill at present day Idlewild</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div>

<script id="script-row-unique-6" data-row="script-row-unique-6" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-6"));</script></div></div></div>




<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-7"><div class="row col-no-gutter no-top-padding no-bottom-padding no-h-padding full-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-1/5 no-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1658132744002 border-color-gyho-color left-t-right animate_when_almost_visible"  style="border-style: solid;margin-right: 10% ;margin-left: 10% ;border-top-width: 4px ;border-right-width: 0px ;border-bottom-width: 0px ;border-left-width: 0px ;padding-top: 10px ;"><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb251e2350">The Big Thompson River from the foothills to Estes Park was first permanently settled about 1893 when a saw mill was located at Harding Heights [Idlewild] by a party of men which included O.S. [Orren Smith Knapp] and Ira O. Knapp [Ira Owen Knapp].</div>
</div><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1658132966338 right-t-left animate_when_almost_visible"  style="margin-right: 10% ;margin-left: 10% ;"><p style="text-align: left;"><em><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb29fe2351">Ira O. Knapp, Glen Haven, History of the Big Thompson Canyon, 1939</div></em></p>
</div><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1617356820233 border-color-gyho-color right-t-left animate_when_almost_visible"  style="border-style: solid;margin-right: 10% ;margin-left: 10% ;border-top-width: 0px ;border-right-width: 0px ;border-bottom-width: 1px ;border-left-width: 0px ;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-7" data-row="script-row-unique-7" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-7"));</script></div></div></div>



<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/1893-knapp-sawmill-at-idlewild/">c. 1893</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>July 7th, 1893</title>
		<link>https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/rannells-toll-road-two-miles-from-idlewild/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathaniel Dauth]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 02 Apr 2021 14:40:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/?post_type=cool_timeline&#038;p=575</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/rannells-toll-road-two-miles-from-idlewild/">July 7th, 1893</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-8"><div class="row col-no-gutter no-top-padding no-bottom-padding no-h-padding full-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 no-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light shift_y_neg_half"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column alpha-anim animate_when_almost_visible" ><h4><strong><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62d3df9341435">Rannells Toll Road Reaches 2 Miles From Idlewild</div></strong></h4>
<div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbafef995f0">John Rannells builds a toll road from the Pole Hill Road to his homestead in Cedar Cove up to a point just a few miles east of Idlewild.</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div>

<script id="script-row-unique-8" data-row="script-row-unique-8" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-8"));</script></div></div></div>



<div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-9"><div class="row no-top-padding no-bottom-padding no-h-padding full-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-6 single-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light animate_when_almost_visible alpha-anim"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode-single-media  text-right"><div class="single-wrapper" style="max-width: 100%;"><div class="tmb tmb-light  tmb-shadowed tmb-shadowed-sm tmb-media-first tmb-media-last tmb-content-overlay tmb-no-bg"><div class="t-inside"><div class="t-entry-visual"><div class="t-entry-visual-tc"><div class="uncode-single-media-wrapper"><img class="wp-image-1860" src="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1893-06-30-The-Leader-Rannells-Toll-Road-Update-Cropped.jpg" width="713" height="713" alt="" srcset="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1893-06-30-The-Leader-Rannells-Toll-Road-Update-Cropped.jpg 713w, https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1893-06-30-The-Leader-Rannells-Toll-Road-Update-Cropped-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1893-06-30-The-Leader-Rannells-Toll-Road-Update-Cropped-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.idlewildlodge.org/wp-content/uploads/Page-Timeline-Article-1893-06-30-The-Leader-Rannells-Toll-Road-Update-Cropped-250x250.jpg 250w" sizes="(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px" /></div>
					</div>
				</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-6 no-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light animate_when_almost_visible right-t-left"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1658054420531 text-small"  style="margin-bottom: -15px ;">
</div><div class="uncode_text_column text-small" ><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb19f995f3">From him we learned that five miles of good road had been made from Zach Taylor's place to a point about two miles beyond Rannell's ranch, and that work was being pushed as rapidly as possible to complete the road to the Park.</div>
</div><div class="uncode_text_column vc_custom_1658054434023 text-small"  style="margin-top: 20px ;"><div class="vc_acf vc_txt_align_left field_62cbb21b995f4">The Leader - June 30th, 1893</div>
</div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-9" data-row="script-row-unique-9" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-9"));</script></div></div></div>




<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/timeline/rannells-toll-road-two-miles-from-idlewild/">July 7th, 1893</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org">Idlewild Lodge</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
